<p>Outranking franchises with 50x the marketing budget proved that local relevance beats brand size in local search. Google prioritizes relevance and proximity over brand recognition for local queries.</p>
<h2>Chapter 6: The 7 Tactics That Show Up in Every Winning Case Study &#123;#ch6&#125;</h2>
<p>After analyzing these case studies and dozens more, 7 tactics appear in every successful local SEO campaign. These are not advanced techniques. They are fundamentals that most businesses ignore.</p>
<h3>Tactic 1: Google Business Profile Optimization</h3>
<p>Every winning case study started with GBP optimization. This is the highest-impact action in local SEO. A complete profile gets 7x more clicks than an incomplete one.</p>
<p><strong>The GBP Checklist:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Claim and verify the profile</li>
<li>[ ] Select the most accurate primary category</li>
<li>[ ] Add all relevant secondary categories</li>
<li>[ ] Write a keyword-rich business description</li>
<li>[ ] Upload 50+ high-resolution photos</li>
<li>[ ] Add products and services with descriptions</li>
<li>[ ] Post updates 2-3x per week</li>
<li>[ ] Respond to all reviews within 24 hours</li>
<li>[ ] Answer all Q&amp;A questions</li>
<li>[ ] Keep hours, phone, and address updated</li>
</ul>
<p>Businesses that complete this checklist see measurable improvements within 30 days. <a href="/blog/local-seo-checklist/">Our local SEO checklist</a> covers every step in detail.</p>
<h3>Tactic 2: Review Generation Systems</h3>
<p>Reviews are the #2 ranking factor for local pack results. But most businesses wait for reviews to happen naturally. Winning businesses build systems that generate reviews consistently.</p>
<p>The most effective system: send a review request immediately after a positive interaction. A plumber sends a text before leaving the driveway. A dentist sends an SMS 2 hours after an appointment. A law firm sends an email 2 weeks after a case settlement.</p>
<p>The key is timing. Ask when the customer is most satisfied. Make it easy with a direct link. Follow up once if they do not respond.</p>
