<h3>Tactic 3: Local Landing Pages</h3>
<p>Generic service pages do not rank for local terms. You need dedicated pages for each service + location combination.</p>
<p>A plumber needs separate pages for:
- Emergency plumber Austin
- Water heater repair Austin
- Drain cleaning Austin
- Burst pipe repair Austin</p>
<p>Each page should include:
- Local landmarks and neighborhood references
- Directions from major intersections
- Local customer testimonials
- Area-specific service details
- Local schema markup</p>
<p><a href="/blog/keyword-research-local-seo/">Our guide to local keyword research</a> shows how to find the right terms for your area.</p>
<h3>Tactic 4: NAP Consistency</h3>
<p>NAP stands for Name, Address, Phone. Your NAP must be identical across every directory, website, and platform where your business appears.</p>
<p>Even small differences hurt rankings:
- "123 Main St" vs. "123 Main Street"
- "Suite 100" vs. "Ste 100"
- "(555) 123-4567" vs. "555-123-4567"</p>
<p>Use a tool or spreadsheet to audit every listing. Fix inconsistencies. This alone can improve rankings within 2-4 weeks.</p>
<h3>Tactic 5: Local Schema Markup</h3>
<p>Schema markup helps search engines understand your business. LocalBusiness schema, Service schema, and Review schema all improve your chances of appearing in rich results.</p>
