<h3>Tactic 6: Local Link Building</h3>
<p>Local backlinks signal to Google that your business is part of the community. You do not need hundreds. You need the right ones.</p>
<p>The best local link sources:
- Chamber of Commerce membership
- Local business associations
- Sponsorships of local events or teams
- Partnerships with complementary local businesses
- Local news mentions and press coverage
- Guest posts on local blogs
- Community organization directories</p>
<p>One link from your local Chamber of Commerce is worth more than 10 links from generic directories.</p>
<p><a href="/blog/link-building-for-local-seo/">Our link building guide for local SEO</a> covers proven tactics for every industry.</p>
<h3>Tactic 7: Consistent Content Publishing</h3>
<p>Businesses that publish local content consistently outperform those that do not. The content does not need to be long. It needs to be relevant and local.</p>
<p>Content ideas that work:
- "Best [service] in [neighborhood]"
- "How to prepare your [home/business] for [local weather event]"
- "Meet the team: [staff member name]"
- "Customer spotlight: [local customer story]"
- "What to know about [local regulation] for [service]"</p>
<p>The key is consistency. One post per week is better than 10 posts in one week and then nothing for 3 months.</p>
